default1.b. 
defaultOrganizationaldefault Profile defaultThe Arava Institute makes an ongoing and innovative contribution to peace education 
defaultand social justice through its mission to train the next generation of environmental leaders in the Middle East to work together to solve critical regional challenges. Since 1996, the Arava Institute has educated over 800 environmental and social justice l
defaulteaders who have the technical literacy and practical skills to build a more peaceful and sustainable 
defaultMiddle
default East.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Arava Institute for Environmental Studies (AIES) —one of the leading environmental academic and research institutions in the Middle East—
default challenges the mindset that peace and cooperation cannot be achieved in the Middle East. Even in times of conflict, AIES provides a positive paradigm for relationships between Jews and Arabs in the region, one that builds trust and understanding. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAIES is the only nongovernmental organization in the Middle East to provide Jews and Arabs 
defaultfrom the region 
defaultthe opportunity to live, study and work together. Many students arrive with fears and trepidation about meeting “the other” for the first time
default. The 
defaultA
defaultrava Institute 
defaulthelps 
defaulttransform these
default misperceptions and fears into friendships and understanding, and most importantly into trusting partnerships that sustain, even in the 
defaultface of conflict. 
default 
default A quote from 
defaulta 
defaultPalestinian alumna expresses these achievements: 
default“We are not just talking about it, we are doing it. We are changing things together.” 
