default2.a
default. 
defaultPeacebuilding and Environmental Leadership Seminar - 
defaultPELS
defaultThe Peacebuilding and Environmental Leadership S
defaulteminar (PELS)
default 
defaultis a compulsory, non-credit component of the Institute's academic studies 
defaultprogramme
default that consists of discussions, workshops, guest lectures and field trips that provides a safe forum for students to investigate aspects of the social and political context in which environmental problems develop, as well as the kinds of relationships neede
defaultd to foster a more just, peaceful and ecologically secure future.
default 
defaultPELS creates a facilitated forum for participants to express their views on race, religion, culture, identity
default, history
default and the current political situation. Participants gain a deeper unders
defaulttanding of the cultural and political sensitivities inherent in such discussions, as well as gain leadership and communication skills needed to establish and maintain cooperation across the region.
